<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">ITEM:&nbsp; HYDRAULIC PUMP UNIT<br />NSN:&nbsp; 4320-01-618-6603<br />MFR/CAGE/PART NO:&nbsp; GORMAN-RUPP CO., DBA MANSFIELD DIVISION&nbsp;(25567) P/N 03H14A-HYD/S1<br />INSPECTION/ACCEPTANCE:&nbsp; ORIGIN/ORIGIN<br />FOB:&nbsp; DESTINATION<br />PACKAGING:&nbsp; MILITARY/A<br />MINIMUM/MAXIMUM QUANTITY:&nbsp; 90 EACH/2,250 EACH<br /><br />KIND OF CONTRACT:&nbsp; FIRM FIXED PRICE<br /><br />The solicitation will post on/about 22 July&nbsp;2019, with offers due on/about&nbsp;21 August&nbsp;2019 (see solicitation for actual offer due date).&nbsp; <span style="mso-spacerun: yes">&nbsp;</span>Offerors are encouraged to check the FBO website on a regular basis for any updates to the solicitation.<br /><br />The solicitation contains DLAD provision 52.215-9023, entitled 'Reverse Auction,' which allows for the use of reverse auction as a pricing technique.&nbsp; After the solicitation closes, the contracting officer will determine if a reverse auction will be held.&nbsp; If a reverse auction is held, contractors must be registered in the reverse auction system in order to participate in the auction.&nbsp; Additionally, the contractor representative participating in the auction must have taken the on-line reverse auction training prior to the auction.&nbsp; Registration, on-line training, and other information regarding the reverse auction can be found at </span><a href="https://dla.procurexinc.com/"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">https://dla.procurexinc.com</span></a><span style="FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">.&nbsp; Any questions related to the reverse auction system or process can be directed to the contract specialist.&nbsp;</span></p>

36C25019Q1037-NOTICE OF INTENT- BORESCOPE-CINCINNATI VAMC

The VISN 10, Network Contracting Office (NCO 10) hereby gives notice of the Government s intent to award a sole source contract to a VIP Verified Veteran-Owned Small Business, Advanced Inspection Technologies, Inc: 2020 W Eau Gallie Blvd, Melbourne, FL 32935.  The Government believes that Advanced Inspection Technologies, Inc is a responsible Veteran Owned Small Business and Public Law 109-461 and FAR 6.302-5 is the VA s authority to sole source. The assigned NAICS is 339113, and the FSC is 6515. The proposed contract action will satisfy a procurement need for the Cincinnati VA Medical Center: 3200 Vine Street, Cincinnati, OH 45220.  The following items will be procured:

Zibra Milliscope HD Fiberscope (MPN: HDF07.1025.00F6) 2 ea.;
Zibra Milliscope HD Fiberscope (MPN: HDF15.1025.00F) 4 ea.; 
Zibra Milliscope HD Fiberscope (MPN: HDF05.1025.00F) 1 ea.;
Zibra Milliscope HD Base Unit (MPN: 50500) 5 ea.;
Zibra Milliscope HD Zoom Camera Handle (MPN: 50501) 5 ea.

Please do not request a copy of a solicitation.  This notice is neither a request for competitive proposals, nor is it a solicitation of offers. Any response to this notice must demonstrate clear and convincing evidence that competition would be advantageous to the Government and any capability statement provided must address services listed above. 
Written communication received will be considered solely for the purpose of determining whether to conduct a competitive procurement. If no affirmative written response is received on or before Monday June 8,2019 11:59PM EST, the contract will be awarded without further notice.  No telephone inquiries will be accepted.  Inquiries will only be accepted via email at Ronetta.Sweeney@va.gov.  A determination by the Government to not compete this requirement based on responses to this notice is solely within the discretion of the Government. 
THIS SYNOPSIS WILL BE USED TO SATISFY THE REQUIREMENT OF FAR 5.101; AND DOES NOT COMMIT THE GOVERNMENT TO CONTRACT FOR ANY SUPPLY OR SERVICE.  THE GOVERNMENT WILL NOT PAY FOR ANY INFORMATION OR ADMINISTRATIVE COSTS INCURRED IN RESPONSE TO THIS SYNOPSIS.

